  "commentary": "With SPX at 7026.96 sitting between the max negative gamma at 7015 and max positive gamma at 7050, dealers are currently in a neutral hedging zone but approaching the heavy selling wall. The PIN regime with massive positive GEX walls stacked above (7030, 7035, 7050) suggests dealers will aggressively sell any push toward 7050, while the 7015 negative gamma pocket provides buying support on dips. Key levels to watch are 7015 (dealer buying kicks in) and 7050 (heavy dealer selling pressure), with the tight 35-point range creating a high-probability mean reversion setup.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pinned between 7015-7050 with strong resistance to big moves in either direction.",
